Sample Integration of¶

Data source (CELLxGENE)

  • Lengyel et al. (2022) Cell Reports - https://cellxgene.cziscience.com/collections/d36ca85c-3e8b-444c-ba3e-a645040c6185

Note: The assays were different between the two studyes (Fan 10x 3' v2, Lengyel 10x 3' v3).

In [3]:
tic()
total_langyel <- ncol(ovary_langyel)
num_cells_langyel <- round(total_langyel * 0.1)

total_fan <- ncol(ovary_fan)
num_cells_fan <- round(total_fan * 0.1)

set.seed(1234) #
keep_langyel <- sample(Cells(ovary_langyel), size = num_cells_langyel); print(length(keep_langyel))
keep_fan <- sample(Cells(ovary_fan), size = num_cells_fan); print(length(keep_fan))

ovary_langyel_downsampled <- subset(ovary_langyel, cells = keep_langyel)
ovary_fan_downsampled <- subset(ovary_fan, cells = keep_fan)

ovary_langyel_downsampled <- FindVariableFeatures(ovary_langyel_downsampled)
ovary_fan_downsampled <- FindVariableFeatures(ovary_fan_downsampled)
toc()

In [11]:
top_cmarker_gene <- ovary_merged.markers %>% group_by(cluster) %>% slice_max(n = 1, order_by = avg_log2FC)

Based on the FeaturePlot, most of the top cluster marker genes do not seem to be matching the regions corresponding to their clusters with the exception of the clusters 4-8. Looking back at the first 2 plots showing the UMAP, it could potentially be that clusters 4-8 are mostly coming from the same donor.

In [12]:

VlnPlot offers a better view of the expression levels of the genes within Seurat clusters. Specifically, DoHeatmap may indicate that better separation observed in 4-8 could potentially be due to a lower number of cell memberships that would allow the clusters to be more homogeneous.

#total count for each cluster_id across the entire dataset
cluster_totals <- ovary_merged@meta.data %>% count(seurat_clusters) %>% rename(total_by_cluster = n)

donor_totals <- ovary_merged@meta.data %>% count(donor_id, seurat_clusters) %>%
  group_by(donor_id) %>% mutate(total_by_donor = sum(n), freq_by_donor = n / total_by_donor) %>%
  ungroup()

left_join(donor_totals, cluster_totals, by = "seurat_clusters") %>%
  mutate(freq_by_cluster = n / total_by_cluster) %>%
  group_by(donor_id) %>%
  arrange(donor_id, desc(freq_by_donor)) %>% slice(1) %>%
  ungroup()
